data.title: The best place in Victoria for a steak!
data.text: We have tried many restaurants in Victoria for a steak and we keep coming back here for a steak, they are the best place in town. The whipped potatoes that come with dinner are just okay, they are missing some seasoning. Our biggest complaint is that this upscale restaurant doesn't serve espresso... we would love to enjoy a decaf espresso after dinner!

data.title: Amazing food and nice people!
data.text: Sendera is one of my favorites to visit when in Victoria, TX!! Delicious food and amazing service!! It's a must visit!

data.title: Great food and great views.
data.text: This is at the top of 1 O'Connor building the tallest building in Victoria by far.  The food is very good and the view of the city at twilight is beautiful.

data.title: Great decor
data.text: It has several things going for it - like the atmosphere,scenery,and decor. However, the food is average. The good news is that the prices are in line with the quality. It always feels special to be in the top floor of the tallest building in Victoria!

data.title: Fantastic place for lunch!
data.text: Shrimp bbq toast and the tea pork chop were both delicious.  Lunch prices are great!  Service is good.  Noone in town can beat that view!  Dinner is way overpriced, but the atmosphere is special.  We'll keep this as our lunch spot.

data.title: Top of Victoria
data.text:
The Restaurant is on the 12 th Floor.
You are greeted by Erin the Manager.
Beautiful and elegant restaurant.
Our waiter Vincent did a great job.
The food was very good and reasonable. The wine list has 3 Texas Wines and they are expanding the selections. Way to go Erin. Support Texas

data.title: Great atmosphere Great food
data.text: Located on the 12th floor of one O'Connor plaza, The Sendera makes for a  unique dining experience. Although pricey, the menu is filled with  plenty of 5 star choices . Atmosphere is "fine dining" and the views from tables by the windows make for a great dining experience.

data.title: Great Food - Great View
data.text: I have actually been here with my wife twice.  The first time there was for lunch and was a mix up on my food order.  I took what they brought but in the end was a little disappointed. Probably my fault on that one.  Yes, I could have sent it back, but just didn't.  The next time, also lunchtime, the meal was delicious and reasonably priced for a 'nicer' restaurant..  They had us near the window  one both occasions and the view is great.  They also have a Tequila Bar, no one has been in there to serve us on either occasion, including one evening. Yes, we could have asked, but there was an obviously 'open' bar on the other side, so we simple 'settled' for that.  There was nothing wrong with that one but it wasn't "The Tequila Bar". They had 'tequila' there as well.  We had more traditional 'adult beverages' on this occasion in any case, but were looking for the 'tequila taste experience', since it is advertised as a 'Tequila Bar'.  Its not a complaint, but if you care, I would ask about the Tequila Bar as it has been undependable on two visits.  We were told you can rent one of the dining rooms if your anticipated total bill exceeds 'x' number of dollars.  I choose not to list it here because you can call them for 'your deal' but let me say with 8-10 people you would probably exceed the 'limit' to have the private room.  We are members of a Dinner Club (4 couples) and collectively we think we could make their 'limit' pretty easily.  So it's an option for a special occasion or event. The Sendera has a wonderful view of the City of Victoria, day or night and, the restaurant is definite 'upscale' but we saw some VERY casually dressed diners as we observed from the bar.  I have not eaten there at night, but my wife has and she says it "exceeds expectations."  So if you want just drinks, that's a good option and you can do that one of several bars (if they are open) at The Sendera.  Any of the meals they serve have been great.  We did not eat dinner here on this most recent occasion but had some appetizers at the bar and one of those included the thickest sliced bacon you have ever seen and it was great!  We also had the "Pepper Poppers" and they were great too.  Those are items one and two on the 'Appetizer' menu.  Portion size is modest, but we thought just right for two and VERY tasty.  We would recommend either of those and of course they have other tasty sounding options.  It's a good place. Enjoy!

data.title: Birthday Dinner
data.text: We ate here in October of 2015 (sorry for a late review). Food was great, and service was amazing! We were offered a private room for my friend's birthday dinner and the server didn't charge us, how sweet! Had a fabulous view of the city even though it was a rainy night, there was more than enough seating at one large long length table. It made us feel as though we were kings and queens having dinner.

data.title: Special Evening with Friends
data.text: Treating ourselves to an eveing of wining and dining, the service and food could not have been better. The Ahi Tuna was cooked delightfully to my taste (rare), salmon and steaks with accompaniments were delicious as well. The servers were very attentive and respectful of our intense conversation but kept us well supplied with our desired needs. Comfortable and elegant with a remarkable view.

data.title: Had an affordable lunch downtown with atmosphere and a killer view!
data.text: Had lunch here nearly a year ago to the day.  They have a great, affordable lunch menu, and nothing beats the view!!  Our burgers were juicy (not greasy) and so flavorful.  The fries were absolutely delicious, some of the best I've ever had!  Their bbq shrimp appetizer had a fantastic tanginess and everything was cooked perfectly.  They run with a bare bones staff at lunch, so service can be rushed and bland.

data.title: Affordable high end.
data.text: I had quail and other food and drink for about $40. Nuff said. There was a red wine reduction too. Now...nuff said.

data.title: Beautiful and wonderful food.
data.text: Gorgeous views of the city.  Delicious food.  Excellent service.  It was a perfect meal.  Highly recommend the steaks -- just delicious.

data.title: Victoria's Secret...
data.text:
...is at the top of the tallest building downtown. No, not a lingerie store, but a steakhouse, bar and grill with Texan charm. The Sendera and its 12th floor view is not only tops in altitude, but food and service, too.  After having the pleasure of watching some South Texas thunderstorms roll through one evening during and after happy hour, I decided to head back and check out a gorgeous sunset the following afternoon. Both days, I was fortunate to be served at the bar by Payton, a most lovely and charming young lady.  She suggested one of their specials, a delicious 6 oz. filet with grilled veggies and roasted potato chunks.  It was grilled to perfection, tender and tasty.

Glad I accidentally discovered this jewel and now can look forward to a clean, classy, and picturesque place to enjoy Texas craft brews, outstanding food, friendly service (thank you again, Payton)...and a great view on my business trips to the area.

data.title: Delicious Tuna on Salad
data.text: Have had lunch at Sendera twice with friends. Both times I've ordered a house salad with grilled tuna (rare) over the salad and it was delicious both times. Actually cooked to order, which often doesn't happen when ordering anything rare. Great service too.

data.title: Dinner 1/9/16
data.text: Was here for a birthday dinner, dang fine meal. Some had shrimp that garnered rave reviews, Grannie loved her filet. Do wish I'd had room for dessert. When we come back will go up earlier for a drink & to watch the sunset.

data.title: Steakhouse with a View!
data.text: Party of 8 for dinner on 12/23/2015. The dining room was beautiful with nice views due to its 12th floor location. Service was friendly and efficient. The meal was well-paced and the steaks were delicious. A great steakhouse experience!

data.title: Meeting Space in a Bank
data.text: Had a business meeting here. Great view of the city. Wicker furniture....Although it seems uppity.   Nice bar area. Nice meeting space.  We ordered pulled pork sliders. They were average.  Fried green beans were good. Autostart was great. They were very accommodating!  I would schedule another meeting there...but try different food.

data.title: Way too expensive
data.text: Food is below average and prices are WAY high. The best thing about this restaurant is the view of Victoria.

data.title: Steak was good, Rest not so good
data.text:
When I go to a nicer restaurant I like to think that I am paying a little more for things to be done right and that I will have a little better level of service.  On this occasion neither one of these happened.  We had a party of 10 and were seated in a timely fashion based on our reservation time.  All seemed well, we had gotten cocktails at the bar and our waitress commented to that effect and that she would be back shortly.  We didn't see her for 15 minutes and during that time several needed beverages. 
     We ordered dinner and most of us got steaks since that is the specialty.  When our food arrived the only thing that was still slightly warm were the steaks.  They were cooked perfectly and since you always let the steaks rest before serving they were still warm when served.  All of the sides were just room temperature.  We took a poll at the table and they were all that way.  No way that should happen at this type of restaurant.  My wife spoke to the manager and he was very apologetic and wondered but at this point it was too late.  To top it off our waitress was non-caring to the point of being rude.  Come to find out since we had 10 people at our table they added a 20% gratuity automatically.  I usually tip 20-25% anyway but not for bad service.
